</p>
<p>And we can't use this <code>$data</code> array anymore, <code>json_encode</code> is too good at creating
<em>valid</em> JSON. Overachiever. Replace it with an <code>$invalidJson</code> variable - we'll have
to create really bad JSON ourselves. Let's see here, start with one piece of valid
JSON, remove a comma and liven things up with a hanging quotation mark, and that
oughta do it! Now pass <code>$invalidJson</code> as the request body:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="45acca958d">
